👖【Large Wash Capacity&Compact Design】This fully automatic washing machine is equipped with a stainless steel honeycomb-shaped inner tub, which can load 17.7 pounds at a time, and can wash many different types of clothes for you, completely freeing your hands. Suitable for dorms, apartment, condos, RV's, camping and more.

👗【Water Level and Mode Control】With 3 water level: L/16L M/23L H/30L. You could adjust the different washing mode through the wash push-button and control the water level via the switch. 👚【Easy to Operate】No installation and easy operation. Intuitive illustrations and instructions can bring you a pleasant laundry experience. There are 10 programs on the control panel, 8 water level selection and LED display. After setting the corresponding washing program, the whole process of washing, drying and draining can be completed alone.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good product and good utility
reviews.reviewText: This washing machine is perfect for my need as a back up for my apartment. I have had the washing machine down in the basement of the apartment that broke down multiple times in the past few months. Landlord have tired multiple time to fix it and it would break in a few days. I finally decided to get a portable washing machine to keep in my apartment just in case, this have been a great addition to my apartment.This washing machine have been easy to hookup and it pretty much connect and use. The product is decently sized, I would say for a couple you would be doing 2 loads of laundry in a week. I have been using the original washer in the basement, but my wife have been using this machine to clean our delicates and the baby’s cloths. Depending on the load size, you and do a wash cycle in as low as 20 mins. She and I have been very please by the product, would recommend the product!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Washing Machine
reviews.reviewText: I highly recommend this washing machine for the the following reasons: it is easy to use, it gives great results, and it is the absolute perfect size. When I first got this washing machine, I was slightly worried due to the fact that the machines I’ve tried before are slightly puzzling and quite hard to figure out. However, I got pleasantly surprised when I found out how easy it makes each wash seem. It also provides me with extremely satisfactory results. It gets almost every type of stain out, ranging from paints to those from food. This is also the perfect size for most households. It is big enough to store a good amount of clothes in, but it is small enough so it doesn’t interfere with my everyday life. Overall, I believe that this is a great purchase and would definitely do it again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Waste of money and time
reviews.reviewText: First when we got the washer the “rat plate” does not fit correctly, it does not “snap” into place there are two random screws which the Manuel does not explain what they are there for I thought it was for the rat plate but there’s no where to screw anything in. The drain hose was leaking from the bottom of the machine. Turns out it’s just tightly put on there’s no adhesive or bracket to hold the drain hose in. The inlet hose is TRASH! Does not work correctly it was leaking from both ends even with adding plumbers tape. I had to go to Lowe’s to buy a real washer hose. The inlet hose part is cheaply put on as I tried to take off the hose the washer port moves. Cheaply put together the plastic is real cheap! Side note if the washer has too much moisture on the panel it can cause an electrical fire or cause the machine to completely shut down. Also any real hot water will cause the plastic to melt that’s how cheap and thin the plastic is. I got one half load completed >:/

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love this washer!
reviews.reviewText: I have a household of 2 plus size adults and a teenage son. For 3 months, so far, I do all our laundry except for blankets larger than twin in this machine. It cleans better than my laundromat. I drain into my bathtub no problem. My only issue is the fill hose included is garbage, it’s short and leaks like a sieve. Plan to buy a good one. Otherwise I’m so pleased.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars So far so good..
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I just got this 25lb model for my little family of 2, so you can see the size here next to a standard stove. It’s honestly too big for two people, but I wanted to be able to wash bedding without issue. I got lucky, because the power cord JUST reached the outlet opposite the stove, while the fill hose JUST reached the kitchen faucet. The quick connect has both male and female threads and attaches easily to male flat kitchen faucet threads (but you may need an adapter if your faucet is different). After using Teflon tape (not included!) on all the connections, mine is leak-free and can be left on without babysitting. I have nowhere to drain under 10cm (won’t fit in bathroom), so I’m draining up into my kitchen sink. I’ll update if I run into any problems. I did not install the plastic rat mesh below the machine. I don’t have rats and figured it would just be something else to rattle around. It’s powerful, and clothes are fresh and clean!Four stars for now, because the length of these connections is something like 3 or 4 feet, so I imagine some people would have issues finding a place to run it without extra supplies. The fill hose, drain hose and electrical supply limit you to about 3 feet on each side of the machine, while the manual demands oft-impossible floor-level draining.
